== Japanese content ==
{{出典の明記|date=2020年4月}}
'''Tsutsumine Shrine''' (つつみねじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kadoma|Q496080|WD=Q496080|1=Kadoma, Osaka}}, {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|WD=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}. It was founded as the guardian of {{ill|lt=Manda no Tsutsumi|Q11617931|WD=Q11617931|1=Mamuta Embankment}}, and is a Shikinaisha listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}. However, there are two Tsutsumine Shrines in Kadoma, and both claim to be the Shikinaisha.

=== Tsutsumine Shrine (Miyanochō, Kadoma) ===
{{神社
 | 名称=Tsutsumine Shrine
 | 画像=[[File:Tsutsumine-jinja, haiden.jpg|280px]]<br />Haiden
 | 所在地={{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|WD=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Kadoma|Q496080|WD=Q496080|1=Kadoma, Osaka}}8-34 Miyanochō
 | 位置={{ウィキ座標2段度分秒|34|44|41|N|135|36|15|E|scale:10000}}
 | 祭神={{ill|lt=Hiko-yai-no-Mikoto|Q11086120|WD=Q11086120|lt=Hiko-yaimimi-no-Mikoto|1=Hikoyai}}<br />{{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|WD=Q382005|1=Sugawara no Michizane}}
 | 社格={{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} (small) / former {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}
