Tsutsumine Shrine in Miyanochō, Kadoma, stands along the former Manda no Tsutsumi on the south bank of the Furukawa, a tributary of the {{ill|lt=Yodo River|Q1140505|WD=Q1140505|1=Yodo River}}. Its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|WD=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

Its deities are {{ill|lt=Hiko-yai-no-Mikoto|Q11086120|WD=Q11086120|lt=Hiko-yaimimi-no-Mikoto|1=Hikoyai}} and {{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|WD=Q382005|1=Sugawara no Michizane}}. It is said the Manda clan, deeply connected to construction of {{ill|lt=Manda no Tsutsumi|Q11617931|WD=Q11617931|1=Mamuta Embankment}}, enshrined their ancestral deity Hiko-yaimimi-no-Mikoto as guardian of the embankment.

In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} compiled in the mid-Heian period, it was listed first among five shrines of Manda District, Kawachi Province, and was Kadoma's only {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. In front of the torii passed the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Gyōki Road|1=UNKNOWN}}, linking {{ill|lt=Kawachi Province|Q1047150|WD=Q1047150|lt=Kawachi|1=Kawachi Province}} and {{ill|lt=Yamato Province|Q907495|WD=Q907495|lt=Yamato|1=Yamato Province}}, and it drew worship from old times. In the {{ill|lt=Kan'ei|Q1192913|WD=Q1192913|1=Kan'ei}} period (early Edo), local lord {{ill|lt=Nagai Naomasa|Q6958349|WD=Q6958349|1=Nagai Naomasa}} (Nagai Shinano-no-kami Naomasa) merged worship of Kankō (Michizane), whom he revered, and thereafter it was called "Tenmangū." In Meiji 5 ({{ill|lt=1872|Q7753|WD=Q7753|1=1872}}), it was ranked as village shrine.

Part of Manda no Tsutsumi remains near the shrine buildings, with a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=camphor tree|1=UNKNOWN}} over 500 years old growing on top. Until early Shōwa, much longer sections of the embankment remained, but they were cut away by housing development. Through efforts of the shrine priest, part was preserved and designated on March 29, Shōwa 48 as the Osaka Prefecture historic site "Traditional Manda no Tsutsumi."

